maintext:
Woman dies in 2-vehicle collision in New Hampshire
A woman died at the scene of a two-car collision in New Hampshire, police said Thursday.
Police said a 34-year-old woman in a car collided with a Jeep at about 7:15 a.m. in Manchester. A 61-year-old woman driving the Jeep was taken to a hospital and treated for non-life-threatening injuries. Neither vehicle had any passengers.
Their names have not been released.
The crash is under investigation.
